    Home » Teaching SupportTrainingCLEAR provides and sponsors a wide variety of training and development opportunities to support teaching at UNT. For a schedule of these events, please review our calendar. During the middle of the semester, we like to concentrate on working with departments rather than scheduling training sessions. If your department would like to schedule training, please complete and submit the Training Request Form. We offer the following training sessions:  Blackboard Bootcamp, 3hrs Grade Center 1.5hrs Discussions, Wikis, Journals & Blogs, 1hr TurnItIn, 1hr Online Course Design Workshop #1, 1.5hrs Online Course Design Workshop #2, 1.5hrs Courses Review Process, 30min Retention Center (webinar), 1hr Respondus (webinar), 1hr Using Item Analysis in Blackboard (webinar), 1hr  Open labs are held every Friday afternoon from 1pm to 4pm in Chilton Hall 112K. No registration is necessary! Webinar Recordings Miss out on a webinar? View recorded webinars and access materials and handouts here.                 Contact Faculty Helpdesk: Email: clearhelp@unt.edu Phone: (940) 369-7394 In-person: Chilton Hall 112C Site Support: For questions and comments concerning website functionality, please contact: Gabe.Vega@unt.edu             Physical Address:      Center for Learning Enhancement, Assessment, and Redesign     410 Avenue C Chilton Hall 112 Denton, TX 76203 USA  Voice: 940.565.2708                 UNT System:  UNT Home UNT System UNT Dallas UNT Health Science Center               Site last updated on March 09, 2017  Disclaimer |        AA/EOE/ADA |        Privacy Statement |        Web Accessibility Policy |        State of Texas Online |        Emergency Preparedness               
